# Using the Input() Function, can advise the user to provide data into the Terminal.
# Note, we can add a space for tidiness, or force the user to provide their answer on a new line.

input("What is your Name? ")
input("What is your Name?\n")

# We can also nest functions i.e. place a function, inside of another. Below, we are asking the Adviser firstly for
# input. Thereafter, the program will store the input, and print it with the statement 'Hello **Input**'

print("Hello " + input("What is your Name? "))
print("Hello\n" + input("What is your Name? "))
